dcterms:creator: A. Krizhevsky
dcterms:description: CIFAR-10 is a dataset consisting of 60,000 32x32 color images in 10 classes, with 6,000 images per class. It is commonly used for training machine learning models in image classification tasks.
dcterms:title: CIFAR-10

dcterms:creator: Y. LeCun
C. Cortes
C. J. Burges
dcterms:description: MNIST is a dataset of handwritten digits, consisting of 60,000 training images and 10,000 testing images. It is widely used for training various image processing systems.
dcterms:title: MNIST

dcterms:description: The Swiss Roll dataset is a synthetic dataset often used for testing manifold learning algorithms. It consists of a 3D spiral structure that can be projected into 2D space.
dcterms:title: Swiss Roll

dcterms:description: The Synthetic Dataset is a collection of artificially generated data used for testing algorithms in various machine learning tasks. The specifics of the dataset can vary based on the application.
dcterms:title: Synthetic Dataset
